          "context": "CompletableFuture<T> implements both Future<T> and CompletionStage<T>, enabling composable asynchronous programming. CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(supplier) runs the supplier asynchronously using the ForkJoinPool.commonPool() by default. thenApply(fn) transforms the result synchronously on the completing thread; thenApplyAsync(fn) runs on a pool thread. thenCompose(fn) is used when the function returns another CompletableFuture, avoiding nested futures. thenCombine(other, fn) combines two independent futures when both complete. exceptionally(fn) handles exceptions by providing a fallback value; handle(fn) processes both result and exception. CompletableFuture.allOf(futures) returns a future that completes when all given futures complete. CompletableFuture.anyOf(futures) completes when any one of the given futures completes. join() blocks and retrieves the result, throwing an unchecked CompletionException on failure; get() throws checked exceptions. Timeouts can be set with orTimeout(duration, unit) (Java 9+) which completes the future exceptionally on timeout, or completeOnTimeout(value, duration, unit) which provides a default value.",
