          "context": "Spring Boot auto-configuration reduces setup by automatically registering beans when certain conditions are met. Auto-configuration classes are discovered via META-INF/spring/org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.AutoConfiguration.imports in Spring Boot 3. The @ConditionalOnMissingBean annotation skips bean creation if a bean of the same type already exists in the context. @ConditionalOnClass activates a configuration only when a specific class is on the classpath. @ConditionalOnProperty enables configuration when a property key has an expected value in application properties. @AutoConfigureBefore and @AutoConfigureAfter control the ordering of auto-configuration classes relative to each other. The property spring.autoconfigure.exclude accepts a comma-separated list of auto-configuration class names to disable. Custom auto-configuration is packaged as a library JAR that includes the configuration class and the imports registration file. The spring-boot-autoconfigure module bundles auto-configurations for embedded servers, data sources, caching, and messaging. Auto-configurations follow the principle that user-defined beans always take precedence over auto-configured beans.",
